title: First day at the new job!

children.text: Started my new position today and I'm feeling a mix of excitement and nervousness. The team seems friendly and I'm looking forward to learning the ropes. It's a big change but I think it's going to be good for me.

Another night of tossing and turning. My mind won't shut off. I keep thinking about all the things I need to do tomorrow and worrying about whether I'm doing well enough at work. I wish I could just relax and sleep.

Met up with Sarah today. We haven't seen each other in months! It was so nice to catch up and laugh about old times. She's doing really well and it made me realize I should reach out to friends more often. Feeling grateful.

Everything feels like too much right now. Work deadlines are piling up, my apartment is a mess, and I haven't had time for myself in weeks. I feel like I'm drowning and I don't know how to ask for help. Maybe I'm just not cut out for this.
Just a regular Tuesday. Nothing special happened. Work was fine, came home, made dinner, watched some TV. Feeling pretty neutral about everything today.

Had an amazing session with my therapist today. We talked about my patterns of self-sabotage and I finally feel like I understand why I do it. It's connected to things from childhood I never realized. I cried but in a good way. This feels like progress.

Finally hit my fitness goal! Been working towards this for 3 months and I actually did it. Feeling strong and proud of myself. It's amazing what consistency can do. Maybe I should apply this discipline to other areas of my life too.

Big presentation at work tomorrow and I'm freaking out. What if I mess up? What if they think I don't know what I'm doing? My heart is racing just thinking about it. I've prepared as much as I can but I still feel anxious.

All that worrying for nothing! The presentation went amazing. My boss even complimented me in front of everyone. I need to remember this feeling next time I'm anxious about something - it usually turns out better than I expect.
Spent the whole day reading in the park. The weather was perfect. Sometimes I forget to just enjoy simple moments like this. No phone, no work thoughts, just me and a good book.

Things with Alex have been tense lately. We keep having the same argument over and over. I don't know if we're just going through a rough patch or if this is a sign of something bigger. I love them but I'm scared we're drifting apart.

Got so much done today! Cleaned the apartment, did laundry, meal prepped for the week, and even had time to call my sister. Feeling accomplished and ready for the week ahead. These productive days always make me feel better about myself.
Monday morning. Coffee tastes good. Traffic wasn't too bad. Nothing really to complain about but nothing exciting either. Just existing today.

Family dinner tonight was a disaster. My dad and brother got into a huge fight about politics and I was stuck in the middle trying to keep the peace. Why can't we just have one normal meal together? I left early with a headache and a heavy heart.

I GOT THE PROMOTION! I didn't even know I was being considered! My boss called me into her office and I thought I was in trouble but instead she offered me the senior position. All the hard work is paying off. I'm so excited I could cry!

Now that the excitement of the promotion has worn off, I'm starting to panic. What if I'm not good enough for this role? What if everyone realizes I don't know what I'm doing? Maybe they made a mistake choosing me.

Went for a really long walk today to clear my head. Sometimes I forget how much moving my body helps my mental state. Listened to my favorite podcast and just walked until my mind felt quieter. Feeling more centered now.
Rainy day. Stayed in, watched movies, ordered takeout. Nothing profound to report. Sometimes boring days are exactly what I need.

Everyone seems to be busy with their own lives and I feel so alone. I scroll through social media seeing everyone having fun and I'm just here by myself. I know comparison is the thief of joy but I can't help it. I miss feeling connected to people.
